{
  "page": "Fire & Blood, Being a History of the Targaryen Kings of Westeros",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>Fire &amp; Blood, Being a History of the Targaryen Kings of Westeros</b></i> is an uncompleted history of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> written by Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> in the late third century <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/12/Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/300px-Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"259\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/12/Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/450px-Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/12/Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/600px-Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Eustace_Mushroom_and_Munkun_by_Chase_Stone_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Gyldayn's three chief sources for the Dance of the Dragons: Eustace, Mushroom, and Munkun © Chase Stone in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>Only the first volume of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a>'s work is known to have been completed, covering the reigns of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> kings from <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">the regency</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The book incorporates the contents of several of the <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">archmaester</a>'s earlier works with only <a href=\"/index.php/Errata_of_history_novellas\" title=\"Errata of history novellas\">minor amendments</a>, such as <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen,_or,_the_Blacks_and_the_Greens\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen, or, the Blacks and the Greens\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rogue_Prince,_or,_A_King%27s_Brother\" title=\"The Rogue Prince, or, A King&#39;s Brother\">The Rogue Prince</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtrp.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtrp.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sons_of_the_Dragon_(Gyldayn)\" title=\"The Sons of the Dragon (Gyldayn)\">The Sons of the Dragon</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtsotd.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the original texts, after completing the first chapter, covering <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, Archmaester Gyldayn sent a copy to Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_(archmaester)\" title=\"Gerold (archmaester)\">Gerold</a>, perhaps for his commentary and approval. However, this manuscript was lost until Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a> discovered it along with other fragments written by Gyldayn among Gerold's papers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Yandel included this chapter into his work <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, in which he wrote that he hoped the rest of Gyldayn's masterwork would one day be discovered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_glorious_reign.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_glorious_reign.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Yandel's  usage of Gyldayn's text was done with the latter's blessing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Gyldayn drew upon many sources for his work. These included official court records<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and the writings of various <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maesters</a>, especially the <a href=\"/index.php/Grand_Maester\" title=\"Grand Maester\">Grand Maesters</a>, who kept written accounts with varying degrees of diligence. Another key source was the writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a>, the long-time <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In covering the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Gyldayn most heavily referenced three main sources, <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Reign_of_King_Viserys,_First_of_His_Name,_and_the_Dance_of_the_Dragons_That_Came_After\" title=\"The Reign of King Viserys, First of His Name, and the Dance of the Dragons That Came After\">The Reign of King Viserys, First of His Name, and the Dance of the Dragons That Came After</a></i> by Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace\" title=\"Eustace\">Eustace</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling\" title=\"The Dance of the Dragons, A True Telling\">The Dance of the Dragons, A True Telling</a></i> by Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Testimony_of_Mushroom\" title=\"The Testimony of Mushroom\">The Testimony of Mushroom</a></i> as dictated by the court jester <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>. Both Mushroom and Eustace had close ties to the Targaryens and were well-placed to know much of their goings-on, though Gyldayn noted their accounts were often contradictory and filled with salacious rumors and accusations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Munkun, though not an eye-witness himself, drew heavily upon the confessions of the former Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a>, who was, as well as interviews and other sources. Gyldayn considered Munkun's history \" by far the most detailed and authoritative\" and thus referenced him frequently.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, the real life author of the fictional texts, decided to let <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> live into <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>'s reign, so his history book could cover the entire Targaryen dynasty.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gyldayn_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gyldayn-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Hence in the latest prints, Gyldayn shared his uncompleted work with Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Perestan\" title=\"Perestan\">Perestan</a>, who then informed <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a>. Gyldayn was persuaded by Yandel to permit the use of passages from Gyldayn's work in Yandel's book.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The history of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">the Conquest</a> is as complete as any, and that is why I have placed it <a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">here</a>, so that—at last—more eyes than mine and the late Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_(archmaester)\" title=\"Gerold (archmaester)\">Gerold</a>'s may appreciate and learn from it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Fire_%26_Blood,_Being_a_History_of_the_Targaryen_Kings_of_Westeros&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reign of the Dragons.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-GyldaynRetcon-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-GyldaynRetcon_2-2\">2.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/asoiaf/comments/eyf4bc\">When did they update The World of Ice &amp; Fire? (February 3, 2020)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\">4.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The D